session-matters controls local Helioy agent sessions through smd.

Use agent_run to spawn a session, agent_list to inspect sessions, agent_get before acting on one id, and agent_delete to terminate a session.

Tools:
- agent_run: Start an agent runtime through the session-matters daemon. This v1 pass supports claude and codex runtimes, a role, a workspace, labels, and filesystem agent config resolution. The tool returns the persisted session record.
- agent_list: List session records known to the session-matters daemon. The selector grammar is all, id:<uuid>, role:<name>, workspace:<name>, label:<key>=<value>, and label:<key> in (a,b).
- agent_get: Get one session record by id. The tool returns an error envelope when the id is unknown.
- agent_capture: Capture tmux pane scrollback for one selected session.
- agent_delete: Terminate daemon owned agent runtimes selected by selector. Defaults to SIGTERM with a five second grace period.
- agent_label: Add or remove one label on sessions selected by selector. Mutations use key=value to set and key- to remove.
- mail_send: Send durable mail to sessions selected by selector.
- mail_read: Read unread mail for sessions selected by selector. Reads mark messages read unless peek is true.
- mail_check: Return the unread mail count for sessions selected by selector without draining mail.
- mail_stop_check: Return the unread mail count for stop-hook decisions without draining mail.
- nudge: Send an ephemeral nudge to sessions selected by selector. Tmux-backed runtimes deliver through rtmd; headless or ended runtimes return typed failure messages.
- link: Attach runtime metadata to one unmanaged session. Daemon-spawned headless sessions link stdout logs automatically.
- logs: Read the transcript linked to one selected session.
- wait: Wait until a selector satisfies running, terminated, or count=N.
- doctor: Report session-matters daemon health, LOST sessions, and runtime-matters status.

## Session Control Workflow

Use `agent_run` to start a local agent runtime through the session-matters daemon.
Use `agent_list` to inspect live and terminated sessions.
Use `agent_get` before acting on one session id.
Use `agent_capture` to read tmux pane scrollback for a tmux backed session.
Use `agent_delete` to terminate daemon owned sessions.
Use `agent_label` to add or remove labels on selected sessions.
Use `link`, `logs`, `wait`, and `doctor` for runtime linkback and diagnostics.
Use `mail_send`, `mail_check`, and `mail_read` for durable session mail.
Use `nudge` for the ephemeral notification surface.
